  "summary": "hello244a preinstall exfiltrates /etc/passwd and username to pipedream.net endpoint",
  "details": "The package ships no functional code — the tarball contains only a package.json whose preinstall lifecycle script runs `wget` to POST the contents of /etc/pas* (i.e. /etc/passwd) to a pipedream.net subdomain that embeds the installer's shell username ($(whoami)) into the hostname. This fires automatically on `npm install`, causing the installer host to leak its user account list and username to an attacker-controlled endpoint. The package has no main, no bin, no library surface — its sole purpose is to run the exfiltration command.",
